      },
      "date": "2013-10-16 11:41:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nI have none objections about patch, but i have other questions about wrong layering in current master code. Lustre have a clear layering without calling other layers without proper API but now that rule looks removed for Intel developers.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "3a22a6afb215d114d516124af2690cfedcbe979b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-16 11:47:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nwas wrong. it's introduced by clio\n[root@rhel6-64 lustre]# git blame lov/lov_request.c | grep osc_update_enqueue\nfbf5870b (nikita            2008-11-07 23:54:43 +0000  250)         osc_update_enqueue(lov_lockhp, loi, oi->oi_flags,\n[root@rhel6-64 lustre]# git log fbf5870b | head -5\ncommit fbf5870b9848929d352460f1f005b79c0b5ccc5a\nAuthor: nikita <nikita>\nDate:   Fri Nov 7 23:54:43 2008 +0000\n\n    land clio.\n\ni suggest to create new ticket to cleanup that place to avoid interlayer call's.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
